videos.headline: Lynch takes injury-cart joy ride before Cal game
videos.description: Marshawn Lynch rides the injury cart before the game and nearly hits members of the California band before the Golden Bears' game.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_MISC (Lynch takes injury-cart joy ride before Cal game) 2016/11/5

videos.headline: Browning hits Ross for 60-yard TD
videos.description: Washington quarterback Jake Browning lofts the deep ball to John Ross who runs in the end zone for a 60-yard touchdown to give the Huskies a 7-3 lead over California.

videos.headline: Washington scores on WR pass
videos.description: Jake Browning throws it backwards to wide receiver Dante Pettis who throws it downfield to Darrell Daniels to increase Washington's lead to 14-6 over California.

videos.headline: Ross scores second long TD of the half for Washington
videos.description: Jake Browning and John Ross connect once again on the deep ball, this one for 67 yards, as Washington goes up 21-6 on California.

videos.headline: Browning throws his fourth TD of the half for Washington
videos.description: Jake Browning throws his fourth touchdown of the game to Dante Pettis as Washington goes up 35-20 on California.

videos.headline: Marshawn Lynch takes a ride down memory lane... in a cart
videos.description: Before the start of the Washington-Cal game, former Golden Bear Marshawn Lynch makes his entrance by driving on the field in an injury cart, a moment that will go down in Cal history when he drove a cart 10 years ago after team win.

videos.headline: Browning: Anything can happen in November
videos.description: Washington QB Jake Browning joins SportsCenter and discusses his team executing their gameplan against Cal, whether he pays attention to the Heisman chatter, and what he thinks about playing in November.
